[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test structure**\n\nI’m thinking about whether to use a proxy. It looks like it may be best to compile a helper in the same package instead. However, a rule states that tests should remain outside library packages. It’s important not to place tests in the same package to access package-private or internal code. A helper isn’t a test, but having it in the same package raises concerns. Should I avoid this? Maybe a one-to-one mapping could work better?\n\n**Considering dynamic class loading**\n\nI'm reflecting on the one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files. So, does this mean there won't be extra test class files? If so, would a helper file be problematic? It seems like it might break something. I wonder if a Java file can contain multiple top-level package-private classes. But without Groovy test support, what are my options? I could use GroovyShell to compile scripts, but that raises more questions about dynamic class loading. It’s getting complicated!\n\n**Analyzing dynamic access challenges**\n\nI’m considering JVM dynamic access, particularly regarding whether catching UnsupportedFeatureError is acceptable. The challenge seems to be that it requires generating a script class after a native build. Accessing package-private methods feels less than ideal. I wonder if a Groovy script in the same package can invoke static package-private methods. It looks like using the JavaCompiler API to compile a source file into a temporary directory might be a better approach. I need to ensure this doesn’t conflict with native limitations, as it gets quite complex!\n\n**Exploring test helper options**\n\nI’m thinking I could add a test helper source in the same package. It might be a good idea to check if there are existing helpers in the library packages to streamline things. I wonder what those existing helpers might offer and if they could cover my needs without reinventing the wheel. By seeing what's available, I can make a more informed decision on how to proceed with the test setup!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06f812db6eb55f6c016a007f1951d881a197b81fc32a32c134\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAH8psXDUZ1EWCBj1dV9NGTp7UwRlHNfeFlaIcjLvh95iGZlRFm77MM0z0oPdDrFb6zOIvr9dt6Zz1jiWkFWBiNeglHmGVr9SUBoeDg6YGKOqrZc7_BD9NqymjVaiDVbMbBuvcePLgwl99Z9pE27nllOBZQW8tDpZJgmcXPZRn1D_ZZLLKgTZen2l5w0UOoXT8GVbZDdTQ8i08-GGyF_i72zlY0IlWJJ4e2b-DFieiDyuQ2Ez86dTTHg1rrIi2x6w3yiFUrSvAwSX7TB6M-xE6tFvkuFrh8RUd0ejxBvVu53wAwyiEEIWoKW8DvsjE9xJik2JM8ptwEwjg1tHFIW8TfDTtX2IZsGM2YqBl0VN8qKLHWgApJxyl1fRCUqkeaQCF41SIPQ8E5AO_he4EpDWkBWaJ7mz753F2bBjvd6H1ZCPwG_8aXJnEFLcqFurlFiKh-6N_QUaPtYnFyfWWo5cfWGu0jasJKvnU_ltmHWKnUNUYSwIOsFiZF2A2QJ72S_XNFSW4brcHjb6_GwVilPuCHzMviL-7yST3QDo3IW3VEFVnwB-GVMaUzRea4ICKaqTOcZLCAKJJRQa4MR4b2LcrYmc-N_A411poiR7G1pVKvB7VaPHbTY_3KrF7CBfb11nivIe6VSI1q32yHAC4-7VR2ph9KsX7jxiwg7O0DflDAc0ku4O8pMMvVvyqHbsnDNY1xd2wrffjQ0VfkmyLfdqYDMVmW6HWDd1yjTCocnyOZQuSUw4Yn39gbfqm-9w3WX7L_Z-BAcXwQabePUbKTceK1hDOjM8R22HLhWR_IJjRTrcxinNbJIRQTWb4a6k7OCgMxJIHakXlCVv5CuUCYYwrDUMbxA7YZBWF2Bd8e5X-3octeClSE0FEbgXsZ9Fb0WTdcsgU56Jbxx0QcATvSW5t0G0Qee69Ohlh9NqSsoOUTm2xPBZRh7rtnp9IpedW0SYYNXy4GeZndrttSYmZ0FVxc-HlgobK_PDcxAyKjTRiAhcwLupMY93GxH5Ua2_r2jANqhNl3seenjnBz1eyGlvP18cNA6svKQjwwDLTCfM6a1f5XNMzXP9CgqZuaaqzvualglpPEJ2dFYbz15iCYjHvNd9Gn1HO0-hllBHKW_-FJzQcuMIxh1jZP9VAucU6HTGy5DYtndUK2yOYsDp9YEJoyQ7cFsDF4LyreaSeII-lvSOOJr0nveK2g8k2TPCno9qk1EUeyi8YkzFg8csN_Zp4EyMUfOx7epEGuTiI-Z9QxDLb0t76SpnOsIprndN2EZrGKeWMHBRB7cUs2bxmdUWY5ZtZBm5nHGDRnUmMUjNIoqV8zrwu_Q0PvGYN4xTu-g-5pMOHl7E4607kw9gpuYNJT2H0bAS5hvO3YkStSIuVWPtvyTbaZytHY587pjY1gw7v2axfG0GGGwhGiXu1cylL7GJuBp6WCM3oqpiVqpaBxOMdIP_uxH_MZNsZSfoiIoasVmZrznij5boqMVeS1UygpCcAIiVwiihTmqgJtrgfOrD_c_JXY7RiMBWDgnWLpYYGe1OhQmwsdh_rcFoH3cGQPnbLa6U-TvaomndCJ8-zC9-bYVmlSZcRHDNzBTV6zXZ-5kzhCwl5EOnFIIvY6dyZIyTLV7-BBm402mTPv4HzdG0v63Dym7DtDTOJA1aKwSLJojkRA1X6d